    "> why is zero routes returned. clearly the metro leaves continuously. There is one leaving at 19:46 for instance",
    "\n\nThe issue is the `calc_number_of_trips=1` parameter — it asks the SL API for only the very next trip. If that trip's \"leave home by\" time is already in the past, the route gets skipped entirely. There's no second chance to find a later departure.\n\nFor example, at 19:17 the API returned a metro trip departing 19:24 from Skarpnäck, but with 12 min walk time, leave_by was 19:12 — already past. The 19:46 departure exists but was never fetched.\n\nThe fix is to request more trips so we can find the next one you can actually catch:\n[Tool uses: fs_read]",
